casebody.data:
Wm. A. MARSHALL, Deputy Comm’r, 14th Compensation Commission, etc., and T. Bromberg, Appellants, v. LUCKENBACH STEAMSHIP CO., a Corporation, Appellee. No. 6787. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 15, 1932. See, also, 49 F.(2d) 625.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges, and ST. SURE, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to motion of counsel for appellees, ordered appeal dismissed for failure of appellants to file record and docket cause.
